title: Driver in wrong-way crash accused of aggravated DUI - AZCentral.com
text:
Driver in wrong-way crash accused of aggravated DUI Megan Janetsky , The Republic | azcentral.com Published 10:15 a.m. MT March 26, 2017 | Updated 7 hours ago Wrong-way driver (Photo: azcentral.com) 88 CONNECT 1 COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Early Sunday morning a silver SUV drove the wrong way on the westbound lanes of Loop 202, resulting in a collision that closed down parts of the 202 and Loop 101 for hours, according to the Arizona Department of Public Safety. 
The driver officials identified as 19-year-old Jahine Gregg was booked into jail on charges of aggravated DUI and multiple counts of endangerment and criminal damage. 
Around 1:45 a.m., DPS officers received reports of the car traveling eastbound on 202 westbound lanes around Center Parkway. Gregg reportedly crashed with one car at Center Parkway and another car at McClintock Drive. Five people were injured in the crashes and were treated on scene for non-life threatening injuries. 
Gregg was transported to Scottsdale Osborne where he was treated and released for minor injuries, DPS said. 
Lanes on the 202 west and the northbound and southbound ramps of Loop 101 were closed for a number of hours and reopened around 6:45 a.m, according to DPS. Read or Share this story: http://azc.cc/2mEeXvW TOP VIDEOS
